== Career ==
After Shakyamuni visited his hometown of {{ill|Kapilavastu|ja|カピラ城|12=draft|12=draft}} and resumed his wandering teachings, Kalpina joined the monastic order along with prominent disciples such as {{ill|Anuruddha|ja|阿那律|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Upāli|ja|優波離|12=draft|12=draft}}, and Nandika (難提迦). Shakyamuni guided him with teachings, leading Kalpina to achieve enlightenment. Renowned for his deep meditative practices and solitary focus, he was described as having lived a privileged life where food was so abundant it was believed to "arise from the storehouse."

